      "span_text": "The malaria vaccine candidate JAIVAC-1 of the International Centre for Genetic Engineering and Biotechnology, (ICGEB [India, New Delhi]), is currently undergoing a proof-of-concept Phase I safety and immunogenicity CT. This vaccine is a combination of amino-terminal, conserved, cysteine-rich region of the 175-kDa P. falciparum erythrocyte-binding antigen EBA175 and 19-kDa MSP-1, adjuvanted in Montanide ISA 720 [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
